com.github.moribund.objects.attributes

Interface FluidMovable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Locatable, Movable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Projectile

    public interface FluidMovable
extends Movable
    A FluidMovable object is an object that can move with a dependence on its rotation angle. A fluid movable object can only move forward or back, not in a direction that is independent of its current rotational state.
